SIMPLE: ishmaelite
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ishmaelite
<hw>Ish"ma*el*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
descendant of <persfn>Ishmael</persfn> (the son of Abraham and Hagar),
of whom it was said, ⟦ldquo⟧His hand will be against every man, and
every man's hand against him.⟦rdquo⟧</def> <rj><au>Gen. xvi.
12.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One at enmity with society; a wanderer; a vagabond;
an outcast.</def> <rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>See <er>Ismaelian</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ishmaelitish</ent>⟦br⟧
